# counter words, a Japanese part of speech

====Usage notes====
In Japanese, numerals cannot quantify nouns by themselves, except, in certain cases for the numbers from one to ten. Instead, 助数詞 ("counter words") follow a number to count objects and events.

For example, 匹 (''hiki'') is the counter for small animals:
* 犬二'''匹'''
*: いぬに'''ひき'''
*: ''inu ni'''hiki'''''
*: "two dogs" (literally "dog two-small-animal")

